My principles of #Fitness #Health & #Wellness :
40% Nutritional Food
30% Mindset (Habits & Practices, consistency)
20% Daily Stretching
10% Regular Exercise

A reminder that we don’t have to be a gym rat or a diet fanatic to achieve health, wellness + fitness.

The quality of our foods,
Mindfulness of our routines,
Our relationship to our bodies,
and moving them daily in a manner that feels good, to me are the key components.
If you are able to exercise regularly in some form, then great. That can be hiking in nature, dancing, swimming, running, yoga, sports, or weights - whichever rocks your boat.

Share with me one thing that has worked for you, and what you would like to add for 2023.

Join me for an exploration of Parts Work! This is one of the most powerful modalities for healing that I have found. Stemming from Internal Family Systems Therapy, this work helps you identify and embrace all parts of yourself so you can become whole. It’s a practice of letting all parts of yourself be seen, heard, and loved. 

This work recognizes that we are not our “parts” and teaches you to live, and relate to them, from your true self.

We will explore this work through many different practices including a special section with actor James Kyson who will help us to access and embody our emotional parts through the medium of acting! 

We look forward to being with you! 

Much Love,
Emily

Dear friends, 
I am making a return to theater since 2017, my first performance reading with @nashrep , a wonderful Theater company in #nashville where I am sharing time.

It's a beautiful and controversial play about a Pastor who decides to share a progressive, inclusive message, and is met with a very different response from his mega-church.

It's a play that shows that Faith in the Universe and understanding of God is something we all have both a personal and complex relationship with -

I am playing the pastor and the play has already opened up so much exploration and conversation - and I hope to hear your response to it as well. 

It is free to the public, and there will be two performances at their TV studio space - we hope you can be there:

Fri Oct 27 730pm + Sat Oct 28, 730pm: 
The Christians by Lucas Hnath 
161 Rains Avenue, Nashville, TN 37203 
(Free to the public)

Link: https://nashvillerep.org/repaloud

This year I am starting the push-up challenge today @ Winter Solstice : 12/21 rather than wait until January 1.

I’ve also expanded it to include different fitness levels so that it feels accessible to everyone: easy, medium, elite:

# = # of pushups. Take rest as needed btwn sets, and try to finish within the (total time)

💥Easy (5 minutes or less) - Start with: 
5 pushups, then
4, then
3, then
2, then
1

Congrats - You have done your 15 pushups!
*Stretch goal: do it twice a day, and you have done 30💪🏾 Do it 3x/day (morning, afternoon, evening): you have now done 45! 

💥Medium (8 minutes or less) - Start with: 

9 pushups, then 1
8, then 2
7, then 3
6, then 4
then 5

Congrats - You have done your 45 pushups!
*Stretch goal: start at 10 pushups, and you have done 55💪🏾

💥Elite (10 minutes or less) - Start with: 

15 pushups, then 1
14, then 2
13, then 3
12, then 4
11, then 5
10, then 6
9, then 7
then 8

Congrats - You have done your 120 pushups!
*Stretch goal: Combine with pull up pyramid (9mins)💪🏾

9 pullups, then 1
8, then 2
7, then 3
6, then 4
5

Congrats - You have done 45 pullups!
Variation: alternate hand positions :
Pull-ups, Chin ups, close, wide, hands facing opposite ways (one out one in), then the other way.

💥Beast mode: Complete both pyramids (Pushups + Pullups) in 15mins TOTAL 

Join me in making 2024 your healthiest year in mind-body-soul fitness.
Love you all, happy holidays - 
James Kyson
